President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New York and has ordered Federal assistance to aid in the recovery efforts from Tropical Storm Isaias, which occurred on August 4, 2020. The Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in Nassau and Suffolk counties. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for funding. Seamus K. Leary has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.